SIGRAD is the premier Nordic forum for computer graphics and visualization advances for academia and industry. It brings together researchers and practitioners with interest in techniques
In addition to the regular submissions concerning general computer graphics practices
Interactive computer graphics and animation techniques are the basis for the sophisticated modern technologies that drive computer games and the associated multi-billion dollar industry. Further
As a special focus at SIGRAD 2015
1) Position papers and/or posters presenting state-of-the-art graphics and animation technologies in the Swedish computer games industry.
2) Academic research concerning novel techniques and potentially significant advances in visualization
